---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import AnimatedDemo from "../components/animated-demo.astro";
import CodeBlock from "../components/code-block.astro";
import CompareCell from "../components/compare-cell.astro";
import InstrumentSnippet from "../components/instrument-snippet.astro";
import { homepageRows } from "../data/comparisons";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

import installCmd from "../snippets/install.sh?raw";
import viteCfg from "../snippets/vite.config.ts?raw";
import privacyRoute from "../snippets/privacy-policy.tsx?raw";
import llmPrompt from "../snippets/prompt.txt?raw";

const shadcnCmd = "bunx shadcn@latest add @openpolicy/privacy-policy";

const features = [
  {
    name: "Policy-as-code",
    description: "A TypeScript config is your source of truth.",
  },
  {
    name: "Build-time analysis",
    description: "A Vite plugin scans collecting() calls and wires your data inventory automatically.",
  },
  {
    name: "Consent primitives",
    description: "useCookies(), <ConsentGate>, and a headless <CookieBanner>.",
  },
  {
    name: "React & Vue renderers",
    description: "Drop <PrivacyPolicy /> into any framework.",
  },
  {
    name: "Multi-format output",
    description: "Markdown, HTML, and PDF from the same config.",
  },
  {
    name: "Apache-2.0 licensed",
    description: "No subscription, no lock-in.",
  },
];

const frameworks = [
  { name: "React", icon: "simple-icons:react", slug: "react" },
  { name: "Next.js", icon: "simple-icons:nextdotjs", slug: "nextjs" },
  { name: "Vue", icon: "simple-icons:vuedotjs", slug: "vue" },
  { name: "Nuxt", icon: "simple-icons:nuxtdotjs", slug: "nuxt" },
  { name: "Svelte", icon: "simple-icons:svelte", slug: "svelte" },
  { name: "Astro", icon: "simple-icons:astro", slug: "astro" },
  { name: "TanStack", icon: "simple-icons:tanstack", slug: "tanstack" },
  { name: "Remix", icon: "simple-icons:remix", slug: "remix" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="OpenPolicy"
  description="The first policy-as-code framework for developers. Generate privacy policies and cookie notices directly from TypeScript."
  ogUrl="https://openpolicy.sh"
>
  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      README.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      OpenPolicy turns a TypeScript config into your privacy policy and cookie notice — rendered as React components, Markdown, HTML, or PDF. Primitives like <code>collecting()</code>, <code>thirdParty()</code>, and <code>&lt;CookieBanner /&gt;</code> wire data and consent controls into the app itself.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-px bg-gray-200 border border-gray-200 mb-6">
      {features.map((f, i) => (
        <div class="bg-white p-5 relative">
          <span class="absolute top-4 right-4 font-mono text-xs text-gray-300 tabular-nums">0{i + 1}</span>
          <p class="font-medium text-sm mb-1.5 pr-8">{f.name}</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">{f.description}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">
      Define everything in one <code>openpolicy.ts</code> config — your policy adapts in lockstep.
    </p>
    <AnimatedDemo />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      01-INSTALL.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Two install paths — scaffold a config with the CLI, or pull ready-made components from the shadcn registry.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8">
      <div>
        <p class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">
          WITH THE CLI
        </p>
        <CodeBlock code={installCmd} lang="bash" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">
          WITH SHADCN/UI
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-2">
          Ships Tailwind-styled <code>&lt;PrivacyPolicy&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;CookiePolicy&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;CookieBanner&gt;</code> — full source, yours to edit.
        </p>
        <CodeBlock code={shadcnCmd} lang="bash" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      02-INSTRUMENT.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Wrap data at the point you store it. <code>collecting()</code> is a pass-through at runtime, but the Vite plugin scans for these calls at build time and populates your policy's data inventory automatically. <code>thirdParty()</code> does the same for integrations.
    </p>
    <InstrumentSnippet />
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4 mb-6">
      Every collected field has to be labelled or explicitly <code>Ignore</code>d — forget one and TypeScript fails the build. Compliance gaps surface in your editor, not in production.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-6 mb-2">
      Wire <code>openPolicy()</code> into your Vite config so the scan runs on every build.
    </p>
    <CodeBlock code={viteCfg} lang="ts" filename="vite.config.ts" />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      03-NOTIFY.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Render the compiled policy anywhere with <code>&lt;PrivacyPolicy&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;CookiePolicy&gt;</code>. Control consent-gated code paths with <code>useCookies()</code> and <code>&lt;ConsentGate&gt;</code>. <code>&lt;CookieBanner&gt;</code> handles display, persistence, and <code>data-consent-*</code> attributes on <code>&lt;body&gt;</code>.
    </p>
    <CodeBlock code={privacyRoute} lang="tsx" filename="src/routes/privacy.tsx" />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      COMPARE.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      How OpenPolicy stacks up against the usual alternatives.
    </p>
    <div class="border border-gray-200 overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="border-b border-gray-200">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 p-4">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-center font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-900 p-4 bg-gray-50">OpenPolicy</th>
            <th class="text-center font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 p-4">Lawyers</th>
            <th class="text-center font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 p-4">Templates</th>
            <th class="text-center font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 p-4">Termly</th>
            <th class="text-center font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 p-4">iubenda</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
          {homepageRows.map((row) => (
            <tr>
              <td class="p-4">{row.feature}</td>
              <td class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50"><CompareCell value={row.openpolicy} emphasize /></td>
              <td class="text-center p-4"><CompareCell value={row.lawyers} /></td>
              <td class="text-center p-4"><CompareCell value={row.templates} /></td>
              <td class="text-center p-4"><CompareCell value={row.termly} /></td>
              <td class="text-center p-4"><CompareCell value={row.iubenda} /></td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4">
      <a href="/compare/lawyers" class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors">
        See full comparisons →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      PLUS.md
    </h2>
    <div class="border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6 flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-6">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-2">OPTIONAL CLOUD TIER</p>
        <p class="font-medium text-sm mb-1">OpenPolicy Plus — privacy infrastructure at scale</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
          Server-side consent capture, compliance checks on every pull request, and hands-on onboarding. The core framework stays Apache-2.0 and free forever.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="https://plus.openpolicy.sh"
        target="_blank"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2.5 bg-black text-white text-xs font-medium hover:bg-gray-800 transition-colors duration-200 shrink-0"
      >
        Learn more →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      PROMPT.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Already have an app? Drop this prompt into Claude, Cursor, or Copilot — it reads your codebase and emits an <code>openpolicy.ts</code>.
    </p>
    <CodeBlock code={llmPrompt} lang="markdown" filename="prompt.md" wrap />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-mono font-medium text-xs text-gray-500 mb-4">
      FRAMEWORKS.md
    </h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      OpenPolicy is framework agnostic. Render directly into your React, Next.js, Vue, Nuxt, Astro, or any other app.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-px bg-gray-200 border border-gray-200">
      {frameworks.map(({ name, icon, slug }) => (
        <a href={`/framework/${slug}`} class="bg-white p-5 flex flex-col items-center gap-2.5 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors">
          <Icon name={icon} class="size-6 text-gray-700" />
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-gray-500">{name}</span>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
